race.comment: Tough race to finish. TAKEN (7) won four in a row over the Winter, carrying 60kg to score at Flemington over 1620m in a tough win last time. He's progressive having never missed the top three and suspect he can continue the streak here despite giving away fitness. ROADCONE (11) did enough fresh at Geelong in a handy 1200m race. He won a couple in a row impressively last time in, one at this trip, and if able to let roll up on speed he can take catching. RAIKOKE (6) was heavily backed at Moonee Valley over 1496m but faded late in a stronger race. Back in trip suits much better. SPIONE (13) was good in the Geelong race first up and is proven at this trip. He's lightly raced and should measure up. STYLISH (8) is off a short spell here with form in decent races that has him in the finish.
